It was discovered that the sun was governed by the same basic principles as other stars: the only factors that drove its activity within the system were its luminosity and its rotation.
The intensity of the light and the rotation are combined to calculate the number of Rossby of a star, linked to the flow of plasma.
A smaller number of Rossby, smaller is the activity of the star in relation to its magnetic inversions.
