The 802.11n standard works in frequencies of 2.4Ghz and 5.0Ghz.
This will make possible your compatibility with previous versions of 802.11a, 802.11b and 802.11g; this to the extent that the base station has dual radios.
The speeds of the 802.11n standard are much higher than those achieved by its predecessors, with a theoretical maximum speed of 600 Mbps.
